OL,3,CAsylum seekers could be housed in
OL,4,Ctraining camp in bid to end hotel use
OL,6,FAs of June this year, around 32,000
OL,7,Fasylum seekers were being housed in
OL,8,Fhotels, reduced from a peak of more
OL,9,Fthan 56,000 in 2023 but 2,500 more
OL,10,Fthan at the same point last year.
OL,12,FExpected costs of Home Office
OL,13,Faccommodation contracts for 2019-2029
OL,14,Fhave tripled from #4.5 billion to
OL,15,F#15.3 billion, following what the
OL,16,FCommons Home Affairs Committee called
OL,17,Fa "dramatic increase" in demand.
OL,19,FA Home Office spokesperson said: "We
OL,20,Fare furious at the level of illegal
OL,21,Fmigrants and asylum hotels.
